{
  "texts": [
    "This reasoning process iterates, recovering from errors by running a generated SQL query, capturing the trace, and regenerating it until the desired result is achieved.",
    "Each \"Action\" that the Agent can use is called a \"Tool\" and is described in the prompt with the name, description and the function that should be called to take that action.",
    "In the context of the SQLAgent, as shown in Listing 7, there are four actions.",
    "The first tool, named sql_db_list_tables, enumerates all tables in the database, allowing the LLM to identify those relevant to the query.",
    "The second tool, sql_db_schema, takes as input this list of specific tables and returns their schema along with sample rows."
  ]
}